# gen120 (rung 19 + rung 16) — bilingual ratchet for hypothesis testing. The same
# code path (induce a rule from the examples, then judge the last transition
# against it) runs from an Italian query: the falsification competence lives in
# the algorithm. Only the cue differs (è coerente / rispetta la regola); the
# induction, the prediction, and the verdict are shared.

# Consistent with the induced Collatz rule (odd branch): confirmed.
> 6 -> 3, 3 -> 10, 10 -> 5, 5 -> 16, 4 -> 2. 9 -> 28 è coerente?
< Yes — 9 -> 28 fits the rule (if even: n / 2; if odd: 3n + 1).

# A violation of the even branch: refuted, with the real predicted value named.
> 6 -> 3, 3 -> 10, 10 -> 5, 5 -> 16, 4 -> 2. 10 -> 6 rispetta la regola?
< No — the rule (if even: n / 2; if odd: 3n + 1) predicts 10 -> 5, not 6.
